In algebraic number theory, it's a classical result that the cohomology of the multiplicative group of units of the ring of integers of a local field with respect to the Galois group of an unramified extension is trivial. This is because the units form a group that is isomorphic to $\mathbb{Z}_p^\times$ (the group of units of the residue field) when the extension is unramified, and the cohomology of this group is trivial.

